  CRITICAL  GHA-EXEC-001
  curl pipe shell pattern
  Files: .../scripts/install.sh
  Risk:  Downloads and executes remote code in a single command. An attacker who compromises the URL can execute arbitrary code on your machine during install.
  Fix:   Replace pipe-to-shell execution with verified downloads and explicit execution steps.

  CRITICAL  GHA-CI-004
  Workflow step interpolates untrusted input into shell command
  Files: .../workflows/ci.yml
  Risk:  Untrusted user input (PR title, issue body) injected directly into shell commands. Attackers craft input that executes arbitrary commands.
  Fix:   Pass untrusted values as quoted data and validate before shell execution.

  HIGH  GHA-SECRETS-002
  Committed environment file likely contains secrets
  Files: .../q7ARE-NLHiXpPRLC7LiCD/.env.example
  Risk:  Environment file with probable secrets committed. Database passwords, API keys, or tokens may be exposed.
  Fix:   Remove secrets from repo, rotate them, and commit only sanitized examples.

  HIGH  GHA-EXEC-002
  Install lifecycle hook executes script
  Files: .../q7ARE-NLHiXpPRLC7LiCD/package.json
  Risk:  Runs code automatically during package install. Malicious packages use this to execute code before you review anything.
  Fix:   Remove install hooks or isolate them for manual review and explicit invocation.

  HIGH  GHA-API-001
  Sensitive route lacks obvious authentication guard
  Files: .../vercel-react-best-practices/AGENTS.md, .../rules/server-auth-actions.md, .../authorize/route.ts
