  MEDIUM  GHA-SUPPLY-002
  Floating dependency versions
  Files: .../q7ARE-NLHiXpPRLC7LiCD/package.json
  Risk:  Dependencies use floating version ranges. A malicious version published within range would be installed automatically.
  Fix:   Pin direct dependencies to reviewed versions.

  MEDIUM  GHA-SECRETS-003
  High-entropy token-like string detected
  Files: .../q7ARE-NLHiXpPRLC7LiCD/pnpm-lock.yaml, .../auth/nextauth-config.ts
  Risk:  High-entropy string near auth keywords detected. May be a real API key or token — verify manually.
  Fix:   Verify whether the value is a secret, then rotate/remove as needed.

  MEDIUM  GHA-CI-003
  Unpinned third-party action reference
  Files: .../workflows/publish.yml, .../workflows/release.yml, .../workflows/ci.yml
  Risk:  Actions pinned to tags instead of commit SHAs. If the action repo is compromised, the tag can be moved to malicious code.
  Fix:   Pin third-party actions by full commit SHA.

  MEDIUM  GHA-INFRA-001
  Container runs as root by default
  Files: .../docker/docker-compose.yml
  Risk:  Container runs as root. A container escape gives the attacker root access to the host.
  Fix:   Set a non-root USER in the container image.

  MEDIUM  GHA-INFRA-002
  Container base image uses latest tag
  Files: .../docker/Dockerfile
  Risk:  Container uses :latest tag. Builds are not reproducible and a compromised image affects all future builds.
  Fix:   Pin container images to reviewed versions or immutable digests.

